===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} ''[[blæd]]'' ‘leaf’, from {{proto|Germanic|bladan}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰlh̥₃oto}} (compare Irish {{term|bláth|lang=ga}} ‘flower’,  Tocharian A/B {{term|pält|lang=xto}}/{{term|pilta|lang=txb}} ‘leaf’), from {{proto|Indo-European|title=|bʰleh₃-|lang=en}} ‘to thrive, bloom’. Similar usage in  {{term|Sägeblatt||saw leaf|lang=de}}, the {{etyl|de|-}} term for a saw blade. More at [[blow#Etymology_3|blow]].

